text: Phoebe bournei is a species of tree up to tall in the family Lauraceae. It is endemic to China, where it occurs in Fujian, Guangdong, Guangxi, Guizhou, Hainan, Hubei, and Jiangxi provinces. It is threatened by habitat loss. The species is under second-class national protection in China. ==References== Category:Endemic flora of China Category:Trees of China bournei) Category:Near threatened plants Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
